"Data analytics is a way to record the steps and processes involved in analyzing data to solve problems and make decisions. Data analytics can help companies make better decisions and grow. \n\nSteps in data analytics:\nUnderstand the business problem: Define the problem you want to solve\n\nAnalyze data requirements: Determine what data is needed to solve the problem\nCollect data: Gather relevant data from various sources\nClean data: Fix or remove incorrect, corrupted, or incomplete data\nPrepare data: Organize the data into a usable format\nAnalyze data: Use statistical methods or modeling techniques to answer questions\nVisualize data: Present the data in a way that's easy to understand\nCommunicate results: Interpret the results and share them with others\n\n\nTypes of data analytics:\nDescriptive analysis\nSummarizes and organizes data to describe the current situation\nPredictive analysis\nUses data to predict future outcomes\nDiagnostic analysis\nAnalyzes data to understand why something happened\nPrescriptive analysis\nUses insights from other types of analysis to make recommendations\n\n#\n…more"
