"Nobody tells you this, but data cleaning and data preparation are the single most important—and often the most challenging—phases of any data science project life cycle.\n\nRaw data is messy—filled with inconsistencies, missing values, duplicates, and outliers that can significantly impact the quality of your analysis. Without properly cleaning and structuring your data, even the most advanced machine learning models will produce unreliable results.\n\nInstead of rushing to build complex models, focus on mastering data understanding and preparation. Learn how to handle missing data, detect anomalies, engineer meaningful features, and transform raw datasets into structured, high-quality inputs. A well-prepared dataset is more valuable than an overcomplicated model trained on poor data.\n\nStrong data preparation skills will set you apart as a data professional and ensure that your insights drive real impact.\n…more"
