"Wondering what sets these data roles apart? Here’s a quick breakdown:\nData Scientist 🧑‍💻\nWhat they do: Build models and use data to make predictions.\nSkills: Machine learning, programming, and statistics.\nGoal: Turn data into insights that help businesses make decisions.\nData Engineer 🛠️\nWhat they do: Build and manage systems to store and process data.\nSkills: Databases, cloud platforms, and coding.\nGoal: Make sure data is clean, organized, and ready for use.\nData Analyst 📊\nWhat they do: Analyze data to find trends and create reports.\nSkills: SQL, Excel, and data visualization.\nGoal: Help businesses understand data and make informed decisions.\nIn short:\nData Scientists make predictions from data.\nData Engineers build systems to store and manage data.\nData Analysts turn data into understandable insights.\n\n…more"
