"𝑹𝒐𝒂𝒅𝒎𝒂𝒑 𝒕𝒐 𝑴𝒂𝒔𝒕𝒆𝒓 𝑺𝑸𝑳 & 𝑷𝒚𝒕𝒉𝒐𝒏 𝒇𝒐𝒓 𝑫𝒂𝒕𝒂 𝑬𝒏𝒈𝒊𝒏𝒆𝒆𝒓𝒊𝒏𝒈.\n\n\n\n\n\nIf you’re aiming for a Data Engineering role, SQL and Python are your best friends. Here's a clear roadmap to help you level up and land that role:\n\n\n📊 Step 1: Master SQL\n\n- Basic Queries: Start with the core concepts—SELECT, WHERE, JOIN, GROUP BY, and filtering.\n- Advanced SQL: Learn subqueries, window functions, and optimize complex queries.\n- Database Design: Understand relational databases, indexing, and normalization.\n- Practice: Platforms like LeetCode, SQLZoo, and Mode Analytics will sharpen your skills with real-world exercises.\n\n🐍 Step 2: Dive into Python\n\n- Core Python: Get comfortable with variables, loops, functions, and control flow.\n- Data Manipulation: Master Pandas and NumPy to handle large datasets efficiently.\n- Automation: Learn how to automate data processing tasks using Python scripts.\n- API Interaction: Gain hands-on experience working with APIs and web scraping tools like requests and BeautifulSoup.\n\n💡 Consistency is key: Keep practicing, apply your skills to real projects, and stay curious!\n\nSQL and Python are the foundation, but the journey doesn’t stop here. Master these, and you'll be well on your way to becoming a top-tier Data Engineer. 🔥\n\nFollowfor more.\n\n…more"
