"The best data advice I received this year, did not come from an engineering book. It came from a sales book.\n\nIt's called the problem proposition. Instead of leading with a value proposition, lead with the problem instead.\n\nYour data product has no ""value"" unless it actually solves a problem.\n\nHere are a few examples.\n\n𝗩𝗮𝗹𝘂𝗲 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗽𝗼𝘀𝗶𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻: Single source of truth.\n𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗯𝗹𝗲𝗺 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗽𝗼𝘀𝗶𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻: Never log a ""why does this data not match"" support ticket again.\n\n𝗩𝗮𝗹𝘂𝗲 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗽𝗼𝘀𝗶𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻: Self-service BI.\n𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗯𝗹𝗲𝗺 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗽𝗼𝘀𝗶𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻: Don't wait 3 months for your dashboard.\n\n𝗩𝗮𝗹𝘂𝗲 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗽𝗼𝘀𝗶𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻: Data-driven decision making.\n𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗯𝗹𝗲𝗺 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗽𝗼𝘀𝗶𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻: A successful business doesn't run on hunches and guesses.\n\nInstead of ""providing value"", solve the problem.\n\nStay sharp.\n…more"
